      {
        "id": 1905507,
        "name": "Stan Stevenson",
        "username": "S_Stevenson",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/s_stevenson/{size}/2620_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-04-09T18:49:12.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Richard Albert\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Richard Albert:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Stan,<br>\nConsidering the greats from 1968, 1970 and 1974, Joe might have had some to sell\u2026<br>\nAll three consecutive vintages were excellent for Heitz, but the '69 has lagged behind in reception, reputation and pricing.<br>\nGlad to hear it is still going strong as are so many of the older Martha\u2019s.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Personally, I always preferred the '70.  Had all 4 of those wines ('68, '69, '70 and '74) many, many times.  I will say, however, that the '69 had the best balance of the 4.</p>",
        "post_number": 8,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 10,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-02T17:00:17.080Z",
